37:42.424 --> 37:44.907
there. Actually, that doesn't turn out to be 
correct, but almost. So it was,

37:51.338 --> 37:59.667
well, it's a highly emotional scene, the first one 
you see. You

37:59.768 --> 38:20.451
think of the forces of nature that you didn't know 
about, and how great they are, or what great

37:59.768 --> 38:20.451
magnitude they are. It shakes

38:21.798 --> 38:30.510
you a bit.

38:30.530 --> 38:37.178
Did you change over time when you saw more and more 
of these?

38:40.022 --> 38:40.944
No, I didn't. It grew.

38:45.288 --> 38:54.497
Because that explosion I think was around twenty 
megatons as I remember, more or less that anyhow. I

38:54.517 --> 38:57.660
mean twenty kilotons.

38:58.621 --> 39:09.152
I went on to see explosions of many megatons under 
various circumstances.

39:09.172 --> 39:15.058
And that first flash is always the same. It's just 
bigger and more telling on your mind.

39:27.194 --> 39:31.819
There were British advisors at that test, weren't 
there? There were. British, not advisors, but

39:32.980 --> 39:36.885
witnesses at that test? Yes, there were. French, 
too? Yes, there were, well there were several,

39:38.687 --> 39:44.174
many foreign countries there. Were the Russians 
invited? Yes, Russian was right on board my ship.

39:48.894 --> 39:52.778
He was standing on deck with me when we watched it go 
up. What was his comment? Not so big. Not so big?

39:57.383 --> 39:57.803
That's what he said? That's all he said. Not so big.

40:07.394 --> 40:08.475
Not so big. Some people have contended that we 
invited the Russians to this to make sure that They

40:16.328 --> 40:22.558
saw what would happen to them if they didn't come to 
some post-war agreements with us. I can't answer

40:24.161 --> 40:27.487
that. I don't know why they were invited. Of 
course, the Russians were not the only ones. There

40:31.273 --> 40:32.515
were a lot of others.

40:40.325 --> 40:48.692
So

40:40.325 --> 40:48.692
I can't answer that. I was in the Joint Staff and 
relatively new at it at that time, so I don't know

40:48.732 --> 40:57.400
what the rationale was. Okay. I'd like to know 
about

40:59.382 --> 41:05.687
selling atomic energy. During the 1950s, the 
government carried out a

41:09.772 --> 41:30.478
campaign, basically, and a lot of companies did, 
an attempt to convince the American public that

41:09.772 --> 41:30.478
atomic energy was not only safe, but it might 
resolve a number of the questions like power and

41:09.772 --> 41:30.478
energy. And I was wondering if at the Special 
Weapons Project or at the AEC, if you were in any way

41:33.869 --> 41:42.022
involved with some of those campaigns? Yes, not at 
the Special Weapons Project, because we were

41:43.564 --> 41:54.842
concerned solely with weapons and power reactors 
for military purposes.

41:59.249 --> 42:00.872
But in AEC, And as general manager, well, yes, I was 
deeply involved in all of those campaigns. Not so

42:08.034 --> 42:10.858
much in trying to sell someone something. Our job, 
the whole purpose of creating the Atomic Energy

42:13.381 --> 42:28.682
Commission was to provide a means of developing 
atomic energy from its early status there. to

42:29.506 --> 42:32.390
peaceful applications for MADCON. All of us 
firmly believed that it had the capacity for that

42:33.832 --> 42:41.163
application and for achieving that goal. And we 
spent a lot of taxpayers' dollars to get there. And

42:49.255 --> 42:56.425
what we really were doing was defending our 
actions in developing the nuclear energy for

42:57.181 --> 43:03.487
peaceful purposes. And we're not consciously on a 
campaign to sell it, except to convince people,

43:04.588 --> 43:25.129
particularly Congress, that we were on the right 
track in development in the best interest of the

43:04.588 --> 43:25.129
United States. And in spite of the fact that 
nuclear energy has taken a tremendous back step, I

43:25.598 --> 43:36.071
still think that we were right at that time. And if 
we had continued to have support as we did, well,

43:37.353 --> 43:50.509
during the time that I was there and before that,

43:37.353 --> 43:50.509
half of the Power in the United States would not be 
coming from nuclear energy, and it would be half

43:50.725 --> 43:57.854
the price it is right now. And many, many other 
applications, too.

44:05.664 --> 44:18.960
The fact that people's hands have been tied in

44:05.664 --> 44:18.960
the development of the peaceful applications of 
nuclear energy, particularly in power, to me is a

44:19.092 --> 44:29.807
crime against the United States that is 
unforgivable.

44:35.755 --> 44:44.988
It demonstrates to me a gullibility of some of our 
people that makes me sick. Well, what about the

44:45.008 --> 44:46.770
argument course that many opponents of nuclear 
energy say in contemporary America, and that is

44:47.189 --> 44:56.741
that they point to Three Mile Island. They point to 
Three Mile Island and the accident we had there a

44:58.223 --> 45:02.488
couple of years ago. What's bad about Three Mile 
Island? I'm just asking you. Well, I'm telling

45:07.595 --> 45:08.636
you. I mean, I'm saying that this would be the 
question, I think, to somebody who points to Three

45:08.937 --> 45:16.386
Mile Island. you tell me what happened at Three 
Mile Island that was bad. So far as I can find, not a

45:20.709 --> 45:23.313
damn thing. The only thing that was bad about Three 
Mile Island is that some people got out among the

45:24.455 --> 45:43.943
populace who lived close by, whipped them up to a 
fever pitch, and got them going all about nothing,

45:24.455 --> 45:43.943
and caused a hell of a big problem.

